The OpenStreetMap API returns the postal code in a JSON format as well. Here's an example of what the API call might look like:

{"postalcode": "10001", "name": "New York City", "city": "New York City", "county": "New York", "state": "NY", "country": "United States", "continent": "North America", "latitude": "40.7128", "longitude": "-74.0060"}

The Geocode.io API returns the postal code in a JSON format as well. Here's an example of what the API call might look like:

{"address": "New York City, NY", "postal_code": "10001", "city": "New York City", "state": "NY", "country": "United States", "accuracy": "street_address"}

The MapQuest API returns the postal code in a JSON format as well. Here's an example of what the API call might look like:

{"postalCode": "10001", "city": "New York", "county": "New York", "state": "NY", "country": "USA"}

The Data.gov API returns the postal code in a XML format. Here's an example of what the API call might look like:

<result>
